snippet.textDisplay:
It's going to take quite a while for Eddie to develop a new act. Every unannounced 10 or 15 minute spot he does at the beginning of the process, comedy club audiences are going to lose their fucking minds.

Part of the reason that Eddie has been away from stand-up for so long has something to do with that overabundance of audience goodwill. It must be daunting to consider. Of course, audiences could be grown-ups and understand that their goodwill makes it harder for Eddie to get to the point where he's in a theatre filming his special.

But if people lose their shit for guys like James Corden, we can't expect they'll reserve their mania for Eddie.

snippet.textDisplay:
I doubt Eddie will see this. However, Dolemite was AMAZING
I absolutely LOVED the Dolemite remake on Netflix!

As artists we get told on the daily of what we should do. What we should wear. What we shouldn’t do. What we did wrong...

everybody’s a shit-eating critic.

Well...FUCK OFF

We get knocked down time and time again and get told NO time and time again...

have you any clue what that does to a person?

You don’t like what we do? Fuckin leave.

Don’t watch. Don’t listen.

Dolemite is a shining example of “can’t stop, won’t stop, get the fuck out my way” mentality.

Loved every second of it.

You do you. Don’t let society bring you down.

They’ll try. Time and time again.

Persistence. Patience. Passion.

Wins every time.
Thank you Ed
